{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The hiring by prominent Afghan businessmen of some of the most prestigious law firms says a lot about just how good an opportunity the war has been for many people.", "abstract": "Many Afghans who have been banned from doing work for United States government over allegations of extortion, racketeering, bribery or criminal tax evasion have paid top dollar to lawyers from prestigious American law firms in hopes of keeping their good names, their revenue streams and, potentially, their freedom; they see expensive legal counsel as part of price of doing business.", "section_name": "World", "print_page": "10", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Matthew", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ROSENBERG", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By MATTHEW ROSENBERG", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/01/world/asia/for-some-afghans-cost-of-doing-business-includes-us-lawyers.html", "lead_paragraph": "The hiring by prominent Afghan businessmen of some of the most prestigious law firms says a lot about just how good an opportunity the war has been for many people.", "headline": {"main": "For Some Afghans, Cost of Doing Business Includes U.S. Lawyers", "print_headline": "For Some Afghans, Cost of Doing Business Includes U.S. Lawyers"}, "_id": "5222371138f0d8740ac9cfe4", "word_count": "1191", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2013/09/01/world/sub-lawyers/sub-lawyers-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2013/09/01/world/sub-lawyers/sub-lawyers-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 478, "url": "images/2013/09/01/world/sub-lawyers/sub-lawyers-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/09/01/world/sub-lawyers/sub-lawyers-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "478"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2013/09/01